TY  - JOUR
AU  - Boulatov, Alex
AU  - George, Thomas J.
T1  - Hidden and Displayed Liquidity in Securities Markets with Informed Liquidity Providers
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs123
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 26
IS  - 8
SP  - 2096
EP  - 2137
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We examine the impact on the quality of a securities market of hiding versus displaying orders that provide liquidity. Display expropriates informational rents from informed agents who trade as liquidity providers. The informed then exit liquidity provision in favor of demanding liquidity where they trade less aggressively. Trading costs to uninformed liquidity demanders are higher, bid-ask spreads are wider, and midquotes are less informationally efficient when orders that provide liquidity are displayed. Our analysis suggests that market innovations, which might seem to favor the informed over the uninformed, can enhance market quality by intensifying competition among the informed.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs123
ER  - 



